implications are that high-redshift galaxies are predicted to be more
extended and dimmer than expected before. Secondly, we find that the
scatter in halo profiles is large, with a 1σ
Δ(logcvir)=0.18 at a given mass, corresponding to a
scatter in maximum rotation velocities of
