baryon density, Hubble constant, cosmological constant, and spatial
curvature. We show how observational constraints-e.g., the shape of the
power spectrum, the abundance of clusters and damped Lyalpha systems,
and the properties of the Lyalpha forest-can be extended to a wide range
of cosmologies, which includes variations in the neutrino and baryon
fractions in both high-density and low-density universes.},
