are locked up in stars. The projected autocorrelation function of
stellar mass is robustly and precisely determined for rp {\textless}
{30h-1Mpc.} Over the range 10h-1kpc {\textless}
rp {\textless} {10h-1Mpc,} it is extremely well represented
by a power law. The corresponding three-dimensional autocorrelation
function is ξ*(r) = {(r/6.1h-1Mpc)-1.84.}
Relative to the dark matter, the bias of the stellar mass distribution
is approximately constant on large scales, but varies by a factor of 5
