low-mass haloes but over-predict the gas accretion rates for massive
haloes. Although the models all include both "rapid" and "slow" mode
accretion, the transition between the two accretion modes varies between
models and also differs from the simulations. Finally, we construct a
new model that explicitly incorporates cold halo gas to illustrate that
such a class of models can better match the results from cosmological
hydrodynamic simulations.},
	journal = {{ArXiv} e-prints},
	author = {Yu Lu and Du{\textbackslash}v{s}an Kere{\textbackslash}v{s} and Neal Katz and H. J. Mo and Mark Fardal and Martin D. Weinberg},
