the central density of the white dwarf at thermonuclear runaway must be
as low as {\textless}{\textasciitilde} 2 × 109 g cm-3. Such a low
central density can be realized by the accretion as fast as Ṁ {\textgreater}{\textasciitilde}
1 × 10-7 Msolar yr-1. These
rapidly accreting white dwarfs might correspond to the super-soft X-ray
sources.},
	journal = {Nuclear Physics A},
	author = {K. Nomoto and K. Iwamoto and N. Nakasato and {F.-K.} Thielemann and F. Brachwitz and T. Tsujimoto and Y. Kubo and N. Kishimoto},
	month = feb,
	year = {1997},
